applicationStringKey.description: This is the text at the top of the Loss Event tab in the Loss Event Entry app.
applicationStringKey.value: In the case where a loss event occurs, it is important for an organization to gather the most accurate data possible. Please fill out as many fields as you can, and make sure to fill out all the required fields before submission. Click on the 'i' icon on each section header to get information on how to fill out the fields in that section.

applicationStringKey.name: loss.event.entry.overall.help
applicationStringKey.description: This is the help text for the Loss Event Entry app.
applicationStringKey.value:
When loss events occur, it is often the case that multiple people are involved, or are connected to the reporting process. In order to fully complete this form, you may need to reach out to a variety of people to gather the necessary information. It is recommended that you review all required fields before you begin the submission process, to make sure you are able to provide a response for each.

As an organization, there are a few key pieces of information that we require:
• What Happened
• Primary Caused Entity
• Primary Impacted Entity
• Discovery Date
• Estimated Gross Loss

Please enter your contact information so that we may reach out to you for further information as the event is investigated, and so that we can email you a record of the event that you entered. If you wish to remain anonymous, you may leave your contact information blank.

For further questions, contact your system administrator.
